title: The Face of New York - the city as it was and as it is (Art Hist
description:
pdf / English / 1954 / 180 pages / 51.3 MB

Photographic urban history and portrait of New York City in the mid-20th century, seen through the work of the photographer Andreas Feininger, comparing the contemporary city with images of the past.

'Mr Feininger is not just another photographer. he is also a poet'. Feininger selected picturesque views of old New York from the early 17th century to the early 20th. He then went to the same places and photographed them as they are today. The intro and lively text give a good history of the city
